"On 28 July the Home Office published the Government's Proposals for implementing EC Data Protection Directive 957/ 46/EC. The Proposals follow an extensive consultation exercise, begun in March 1996, and demonstrate the difficulties which the Government faces if it is fully to comply with the Directive without creating further uncertainty, increasing unreasonably the burdens on data users, or denying to data subjects the new protections and remedies to be provided for them under the Directive."
